            "She was nine years old when she told her father that the way he had described a bridge collapse in the news was wrong. Not factually wrong. Structurally wrong. She reorganized the information for him, rearranging his sentence structure until the cascade of failures was visible in the language itself. Her mother was already smiling. *\"Where does she get this?\"* her father asked. *\"From both of us,\"* said her mother. *\"Unfortunately.\"*",
