            "Lakhimi was born in Jorhat in 2010. She grew up between two worlds: the school where her father taught, where knowledge was institutional, and the tea estates her mother visited, where knowledge was oral and lived in songs and stories. She understood early that oral memory was no less reliable than written records, just less legible to people with power. She decided at nine to spend her life closing that gap.",
