            "---",
            "### THE ABILITY",
            "DEVOUR. It attacks the opponent's process rather than their speed. Phantom letters and backwards progress create cognitive interference and doubt. As Priya wrote: *\"It attacks your confidence in what you're doing.\"* Riya agreed: *\"The doubt is the weapon.\"* Lakhimi knows Riya read her journal. She didn't answer whether she left it open on purpose. She just kept writing in her notebook.",
            "---",
            "### WHAT HER TEAMMATES THINK",
            "**Gurpreet** respects her completely but finds her slightly unsettling because of her accuracy.",
            "**Meera** considers Lakhimi the person most likely to understand the complete picture first.",
            "**Arjun** knows she knows things about him he hasn't said. He is less comfortable with not knowing what she's concluded.",
            "**Priya** and Lakhimi have a complex relationship — two people whose methods overlap. Priya is waiting to understand why Lakhimi let her read the journal.",
